<span class="expandableContainer"><span class="truncatedContent">agreed. that&apos;s often my issue with thrillers; i don&apos;t enjoy when the reveal is something that we could never have worked out despite paying close atte<a class="jsShow showAction" href="#">…more</a></span><span class="fullContent">agreed. that's often my issue with thrillers; i don't enjoy when the reveal is something that we could never have worked out despite paying close attention. it seems cheap to just have a backstory dropped on us in the last five pages between two characters that was the basis for everything. oh well!<a class="jsHide hideAction" href="#">(less)</a></span></span>
