        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2899800843" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer16191341415118378474"><br/>3.5 stars<br/><br/>With heat indexes soaring into the triple digits for the past week, the thought of being snowed in at a remote cabin sounded romantic, delightful and cozy. That is, until the dead bodies started piling up.<br/><br/>Reminiscent of the locked door mysteries of Agatha Christie, where there is a limited number of suspects, this was an entertaining dive into the lives and the psyches of the guests at the lodge. I loved the atmosphere of the inn, and the eccentric characters. <br/><br/>Unlike Christie, the clues</span>
  <span id="freeText16191341415118378474" style="display:none"><br />3.5 stars<br /><br />With heat indexes soaring into the triple digits for the past week, the thought of being snowed in at a remote cabin sounded romantic, delightful and cozy. That is, until the dead bodies started piling up.<br /><br />Reminiscent of the locked door mysteries of Agatha Christie, where there is a limited number of suspects, this was an entertaining dive into the lives and the psyches of the guests at the lodge. I loved the atmosphere of the inn, and the eccentric characters. <br /><br />Unlike Christie, the clues weren’t there along the way so there is no moment for the reader at the end when everything clicks into place. Still, this was entertaining and engaging with a surprise ending that I appreciated. Recommended for fans of Agatha Christie type mysteries with a modern twist.<br /><br /> I tried to fill in my reading with the audio version on a long drive and I don’t recommend listening to this one. The narrator has an odd robotic cadence and I agree with the reviewer who said it was like being read to by Siri.<br /><br />•	I received a copy of this book via Edelweiss in exchange for an honest review<br /></span>
  <a data-text-id="16191341415118378474" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


