  <span id="freeText14550881797543860531" style="display:none">This was a ridged and structured book that failed to grip me in any way. <br /><br />The rigidity of it ruined the suspense. Although, I think the plot itself was lacking so that this would still be a three star read for me regardless. It was slow to me, without any building suspense. What we start to learn about each character doesn't necessarily lean towards generating any thrill or more suspicion. <br /><br />Overall underwhelming. I've heard good things about this author and will definitely give her other books a shot. <br /><br />*Thank you to Penguin Publishing Group via Edelweiss+ for providing the digital review copy.</span>
