<div id="review_2632867528" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2632867528" />
    <a title="Lucie" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/78969659-lucie"><img alt="Lucie" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1629831783p2/78969659.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2632867528?book_show_action=true">Dec 23, 2018</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Lucie" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Lucie" href="/user/show/78969659-lucie">Lucie</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=suspense-thriller">suspense-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=mystery">mystery</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=psychological-thriller">psychological-thriller</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/78969659-lucie?shelf=atmospheric">atmospheric</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2632867528" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer338643998346861457"><b>This is an EXTREMELY atmospheric book. A perfect read for the winter!</b><br/><br/>As you&apos;ve already heard, this one&apos;s very Agatha Christie-like. Set in a remote hotel lodge in woodsy upstate New York, the guests are snowed and iced in. The winter storm has caused a power outage which leaves only the fireplaces for light and warmth, creating creepy dark hallways and pitch-black stairs. This one has atmosphere <i>galore.</i><br/><br/>The reader is given a dozen or so really interesting characters to digest, but unfortunately, </span>
  <span id="freeText338643998346861457" style="display:none"><b>This is an EXTREMELY atmospheric book. A perfect read for the winter!</b><br /><br />As you've already heard, this one's very Agatha Christie-like. Set in a remote hotel lodge in woodsy upstate New York, the guests are snowed and iced in. The winter storm has caused a power outage which leaves only the fireplaces for light and warmth, creating creepy dark hallways and pitch-black stairs. This one has atmosphere <i>galore.</i><br /><br />The reader is given a dozen or so really interesting characters to digest, but unfortunately, we are given very little information to actually solve the mystery with. Then in the last three pages, we are given the whole story, LOTS of background info, and why it all happened.<br /><br />Even though the possibility of solving this one on your own is zero percent, it's still an extremely enjoyable read. It definitely kept me entertained throughout the journey, and the atmospheric writing is perfection.</span>
  <a data-text-id="338643998346861457" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


